    <h1>Color Overview</h1>

    <p>Vista Graphics provides comprehensive color handling for canvas drawing operations, supporting named colors, RGB, and RGBA formats.</p>

    <h2>Color Formats</h2>

    <h3>Named Colors</h3>
    <p>Use CSS named colors directly:</p>
    <pre><code>
    pen red
    fill-pen blue
    </code></pre>

    <h3>RGB Tuple</h3>
    <p>Specify colors as [red green blue] values (0-255):</p>
    <pre><code>
    pen [255 128 0]        ; Orange
    fill-pen [0 200 150]   ; Teal
    </code></pre>

    <h3>RGBA Tuple</h3>
    <p>Include alpha for transparency (0-1):</p>
    <pre><code>
    pen [255 0 0 0.5]      ; Semi-transparent red
    fill-pen [0 0 255 0.3] ; Light blue overlay
    </code></pre>

    <h3>Hex Strings</h3>
    <p>Use hex color codes:</p>
    <pre><code>
    pen "#ff0000"      ; Red
    fill-pen "#00ff00" ; Green
    </code></pre>

    <h2>Transparent</h2>
    <p>Use the transparent keyword for no fill:</p>
    <pre><code>
    fill-pen transparent
    </code></pre>

    <h2>vg_color_value</h2>
    <p>Function to convert any color-like value to a JavaScript string:</p>
    <pre><code>
    jsColor: vg_color_value red
    ; Returns "'#ff0000'"

    jsColor: vg_color_value [255 128 0 0.5]
    ; Returns "'rgba(255,128,0,0.5)'"
    </code></pre>

    <h2>Named Colors Reference</h2>
    <p>Vista supports all CSS named colors including:</p>

